  Here's why it earns its place:                                                                                                                      
   
  1. It's the engine behind the Window metric                                                                                                         
  PLI already includes Window — time before the signal becomes common knowledge. Time-Folding is the mechanism that calculates Window without waiting
  for full coverage to develop. Without it, Window is a lagging indicator. With it, Window is a leading one. That's the difference between reporting  
  the inflection and predicting it.
                                                                                                                                                      
  2. It's the technical justification for the Lens pricing tiers
  Why does the Investor Lens cost more than the Student Lens? Because the fold degree is higher — 90° commitment on financial signals requires more
  sophisticated attractor validation than 45° on research signals. The assumption gradient IS the pricing gradient. That's a defensible revenue       
  architecture.
                                                                                                                                                      
  3. It's the moat
  Anyone can aggregate signals. Anyone can build a dashboard. What they can't replicate quickly is a system that commits to a leverage position before
   the room with a structured, auditable reason for that commitment. The fold degree, logged per output, is that audit trail. That's                  
  institutional-grade defensibility.
                                                                                                                                                      
  4. It feeds as-diff                                                                                                                                 
  The fold output — attractor coordinate, confidence band, fold degree — is exactly what as-diff needs to run a meaningful A/B comparison. Without it,
   as-diff compares two subjects at the same point in time. With it, as-diff compares two subjects at their respective fold positions. That's a       
  fundamentally richer comparison.
                                                                                                                                                      
  Verdict: It belongs in the platform. Not as a feature — as the engine underneath the features.                                                      
   
